sections.heading: court; power to vacate or modify judgments or orders
sections.text: (1) The inherent power of a district court to vacate or modify its judgments or orders during term may also be exercised after the end of the term, upon the same grounds, upon a motion filed within six months after the entry of the judgment or ord
